According to the source for trunk, the config code looks like this:

    st->search_cache_size = atol(size);
    if (st->search_cache_size < 0) {
        st->search_cache_size = 0;
    }

which interprets any negative value as the same as zero.

Buried in the cache we have this:

    if (cache_size <= 0)
        return NULL;

It looks like the help message on the directives are wrong, while the docs are
correct.
